@node "INTRODUCTION" "Introduction or why I create this tool"

                               @{u}INTRODUCTION@{uu}

 As everyone knows, calling via bill is not very cheap, and therefor the
 scanning and searching of FileLists is a very expensive job to do. To 
 avoid this, DirDownloader utilities are coded, so that all users could 
 download the filelists and check them out offline. As I uses FAME now for 
 over one year, I had to use Amiex doors to give my users the ability to 
 download my filelists. Well, one of my beta-testers, who runs FAME too, 
 has some strange chars built into his conference names, and all Dir-
 Downloader utilities are using those names as filename for the created 
 archive. This is normally a good think, but *NONE* of those doors are 
 able to check out the created filename for special chars, which are not 
 allowed to insert as FileName!!! Some examples are '>', '<', '/' or ':'.
 Because of this fact I've started to write my own DirDownloader utility,
 which is able to recognize such things...and here it is, DirDownloader 
 V0.2, which has the following features:

 @{b}-@{ub} FAME only door (FIM), so no /X icons required anymore!
 @{b}-@{ub} Auto-Recognition/-changing of special chars inside conference names
 @{b}-@{ub} Supports LHA, LZX and ZIP
 @{b}-@{ub} Integrated Configuration program, no Tooltypes required


                               @{u}REQUIREMENTS@{uu}

 DirDownloader requires the following things to run:

 @{b}-@{ub} FAME V1.4 or higher (therefor Kickstart V37 or higher)
 @{b}-@{ub} LHA V1.38 (incl.), LZX V1.20 (incl.), ZIP V2.0.1 (incl.)
 @{b}-@{ub} Some filelists :)

 Of course you don't have to use all @{u}THREE@{uu} packers, at least only one of 
 them is required to run DirDownloader.
@endnode

