@node "INSTALLATION" "How to install DirDownloader"

                       @{u}INSTALLATION OF DIRDOWNLOADER@{uu}

 Best way to install DirDownloader is to use the supplied InstallerScript.
 If you wish to install it manually, please follow these steps:

 @{b}1.@{ub} Copy DirDownloader and the documentation to a drawer where you whish,
    recommended is FAME:Doors/ to have a better overview for all installed
    doors.

 @{b}2.@{ub} Copy the supplied packers (LHA, LZX & ZIP) to a place where you have
    stored your packers and archivers, recommended is C:, as this is the
    main search place for commands.

 @{b}3.@{ub} Now start the Systemeditor, go into section doors and define a new
    BBSCMD as follows:

         Name: DD
         Path: <YOUR PATH>
        Level: <THE LEVEL YOU WISH>
     Priority: 0
        Stack: 4096
    Interface: FIM Multinode
     Commands: NR, CF, SR, AR

    Don't forget to save this datas!

 @{b}4.@{ub} Now go into FAME and start DirDownloader to configure it. See chapter
    @{"HOW TO USE" link "USAGE" 0} for detailed Informations.
@endnode

