@node "DD_CONFIG" "Configuration of DirDownloader"

                      @{u}CONFIGURATION OF DIRDOWNLOADER@{uu}

 It's quite simple to configure DirDownloader. If you have installed it the
 first time, DirDownloader will automatically show the Configuration screen
 when starting it. The screen looks like this:

 @{b}--------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}

                     - Configuration of Dir-Downloader -

        Path and filename for the specified packers (@=Disable Entry):

   None-Path: [C:LHA.....................................................]
    Lha-Path: [C:LZX.....................................................]
    Lzx-Path: [C:LHA.....................................................]
    Zip-Path: [C:ZIP.....................................................]

  Options for the packers to add files without preserving the dirs:

   None-Path: [-q -z a...................................................]
    Lha-Path: [-P0 -3 -q a...............................................]
    Lzx-Path: [-q -2 a...................................................]
    Zip-Path: [-1 -q -j..................................................]

                     Temporary path to pack the dirs:

 [RAM:...................................................................]

 @{b}--------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}

 The first four lines defines the packers to be used in your system. If you
 want to disable one of them, start writing the line with the '@{b}@@{ub}' sign to
 sign this entry as disabled. The following four lines defines the packer-
 options for the according packer. You should not modify them until you
 have really better options, if you enter the wrong options here, Dir-
 Downloader won't work correctly!
 The last line (temporary) defines the path where DirDownloader should pack
 the filelists to. Of course the created archive will be deleted after
 sending it to the user. 

 After you've entered all the options, you will be prompted if you wish to
 save now the configuration. If you proceed, the configfile will be written
 to disk and DirDownloader continue like when it's normally started. See
 chapter @{"USAGE" link "DD_USAGE" 0} for more informations about the usage. If you have made any
 mistake inside the configuration, enter '@{b}N@{ub}' and you could now reconfigure
 again all options until you proceed the saving of the configuration.


                @{u}CHANGING THE CONFIGURATION OF DIRDOWNLOADER@{uu}

 If you have already configured DirDownloader but you want to change
 something inside the configuration, simply start DirDownloader from FAME
 with the Argument '@{fg fill}CONFIG@{fg text}', and DirDownloader will show you the config
 menu.

 @{b}@{u}NOTE:@{ub}@{uu} This only works for the SysOp of the BBS for security reasons, if
       any other user start it with Argument '@{fg fill}CONFIG@{fg text}', nothing happens!

 Another way to reconfigure DirDownloader is to delete the config file
 created by DirDownloader. This file is called '@{b}DirDownloader.cfg@{ub}' and
 could be found inside the Programdirectory where you have stored it.
 If you delete the config file and restart DirDownloader, it will create
 a new config file with the options and values as shown in the above
 example.
@endnode

@node "DD_USAGE" "Usage of DirDownloader"

                          @{u}USAGE OF DIRDOWNLOADER@{uu}

 When starting DirDownloader, the current conference will be shown and you
 will be asked which Directory you wish to download. The following options
 are available:

 @{fg shine}1-n@{fg text}  @{b}->@{ub}  Selects Directory 1 to n, where n is the highest number of the
          conference.

  @{fg shine}U@{fg text}   @{b}->@{ub}  Selects the actual upload directory.

  @{fg shine}A@{fg text}   @{b}->@{ub}  Selects all Directories of the current conference.

 If you press only @{i}ENTER@{ui} DirDownloader exits. After choosing the filelists
 you wish to download, DirDownloader prompts you to choose a packer to use
 for packing the dirs. If you don't have disabled one of the packers from
 DirDownloader, the following options are available:

 1. None
 2. LHA
 3. LZX
 4. ZIP

 Please note that all disabled packers won't be shown in this selection
 list, so if you have disabled ZIP & LZX i.e., only None and LHA are 
 available for packing. See @{"Configuration" link "DD_CONFIG" 0} for more informations about
 disabling one of the packers etc.

 The None option will only store selected dirs into one lha archive without
 packing them. All other options start the selected packer and compress the
 dirs into one archive.

 After packing the archives, you where now prompted to enter the Filename
 for the archive. After this selection you will now get the archive. As
 FAME supports also local downloads, DirDownloader will also work if you
 use it locally.
@endnode

